| Researchers Chill Mirror to Near Absolute Zero                     |
|   from the barely-moving dept.                                     |
|   posted by samzenpus on Wednesday April 11, @23:50 (Technology)   |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/12/0026252      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "Physicists have managed to [0]cool a
dime-sized mirror to within one degree of absolute zero. This is the
lowest laser-induced freeze yet achieved with a visible object. Laser
cooling involves firing pulses of light at a specific frequency that
exactly matches an atom's motions."

Discuss this story at:
    http://science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/12/0026252

Links:
    0. http://sciencenow.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/full/2007/409/1


