kidcharles writes "The Washington Post reports that in the midst of an
investigation by the U.S. Congress into the firing of eight U.S.
Attorneys by the Department of Justice, [0]numerous White House e-mails
have been lost. Among them are communications from presidential adviser
Karl Rove. Parallels are being drawn with the infamous '18 minutes'
missing from the Nixon Watergate tapes. Also at issue is the use of
Republican National Committee e-mail domains (such as gwb43.com and
georgewbush.com) rather than the official White House domain. This is a
violation of the Presidential Records Act."

